  <static seed="1060" source="PCC-ORCCA-ed3/BasicAlgebra/QuadraticApplications/FlyingObjectApp40.pg">
    <statement><p>A submarine is traveling in the sea. Its depth, in meters, can be modeled by <m>d={-1.3t^{2}+13t-31.5}</m>, where <m>t</m> stands for time in seconds. The submarine <ul form="popup" name="AnSwEr0001"><li>
<p>?</p>
</li><li>
<p>will</p>
</li><li>
<p>will not</p>
</li></ul> hit the sea surface along this route.</p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\text{will}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To determine whether the submarine will surface, we substitute <m>d(t)=0</m> into <m>d(t)={-1.3t^{2}+13t-31.5}</m>, and solve the equation by the Quadratic Formula:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{
        \begin{aligned}
            t \amp  = \frac{-b\pm\sqrt{b^2-4ac}}{2a}\\
              \amp  = \frac{-({13})\pm\sqrt{({13})^2-4(-1.3)({-31.5})}}{2(-1.3)}\\
                   \amp  = \frac{{-13}\pm\sqrt{{169}-{163.8}}}{-2.6}\\
                   \amp  = \frac{{-13}\pm\sqrt{{5.2}}}{-2.6}\\
                  \amp \approx \frac{-13\pm 2.28}{-2.6} \\\amp \approx \frac{-13+2.28}{-2.6}\text{ or }\frac{-13-2.28}{-2.6} \\\amp \approx 4.12\text{ or }5.88
        \end{aligned}
     }</m></p>
<p>The submarine will surface approximately `4.12` seconds later.</p>
</solution>
